video.title: Downton Abbey
video.synopsis: Exposing the snobbery and machinations of a vanishing class system, this series chronicles events in the lives of the Crawley family and their servants.

episodes.synopsis: The lives of the aristocratic Crawleys and their Downton Abbey servants change forever when the Titanic's sinking leaves the estate without an heir.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: The arrival of presumptive heir Matthew Crawley causes a stir at Downton as his decidedly middle-class mother Isobel crosses swords with Violet.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Cora's try at matchmaking is thwarted when Mary falls not for the wealthy Napier, but for his friend, Turkish attaché Pamuk, with dire consequences.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: At the annual fair, Mrs. Hughes meets a former suitor who makes her question her position at Downton. Violet and Isobel lock horns over Molesley.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: As the village prepares for the annual flower show, Isobel and Violet clash. Mary meets a potential suitor, but she only has eyes for Matthew.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Sybil lands in danger when a fight breaks out at the political meeting she's attending in secret. Her sisters notice Matthew's brave rescue.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Cora makes a discovery that throws the inheritance issue into chaos. Pressured by her aunt, Mary keeps Matthew waiting for an answer to his proposal.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: Two years into World War I, life at Downton Abbey has changed dramatically as young men go to war — or avoid it — and romantic dreams are dashed.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: As William prepares to head off to war, Thomas returns to Downton. Meanwhile, Lavinia reunites with an unwelcome individual from her past.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: The dowager countess decides to uncover Lavinia's secret, but will Mary help? And there's panic downstairs when Branson offers to lend a hand.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Violet and Mary wonder whether Sybil has a suitor. Lord Grantham tries to track down Bates, and disturbing news arrives from the front line.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Ethel struggles to cope and, with Mrs. Hughes' help, tries to make contact with Major Bryant.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: The war finally ends, but Mary is under pressure to save her family from scandal, and a Canadian visitor claims to have links with the Granthams.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Matthew has some surprising news, and Ethel introduces her son to his grandparents. But will they offer her any help?
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: Wedding preparations carry on, and romance blossoms, while joy, heartache and tragedy move the denizens of Downton Abbey.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: 'Tis the season, but tension lingers in the air between Sir Richard Carlisle, Lady Mary and Matthew.
episodes.title: Christmas at Downton Abbey

episodes.synopsis: Cora's mother travels to Downton Abbey for Matthew and Mary's wedding. But will the couple even make it to the altar?
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Hoping to be financially rescued by her American grandmother, Mary conspires with Violet to make sure Downton puts on a bigger show than ever before.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Edith's big day finally arrives, but can her family be convinced that Strallan's age does not matter? Mary takes matters into her own hands.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Branson finds himself in hot water over his political views, and Sybil's loyalty is tested. A torn Ethel must make a decision about her son's future.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Edith's exciting opportunity divides the family. As Sybil goes into labor, Dr. Clarkson clashes with a famous obstetrician over her care.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Tempers fray when Isobel's kind gesture backfires. Branson's decisions are scrutinized. Bates' chance at freedom begins to slip away.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Anna's patience is rewarded, Edith has an admirer, Matthew refuses to back down, and Branson's plans for the christening cause consternation.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: A cricket match brings out Robert's competitive side. Violet's great-niece visits Downton, and a trip to London reveals more than meets the eye.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: The Crawleys — with a very pregnant Mary — head to Scotland to visit Rose's family, but everyone can sense the tension between their hosts.
episodes.title: A Journey to the Highlands

episodes.synopsis: As mourning continues, Carson grapples with an unwelcome reminder of his past. Elsewhere, Edith reunites with Michael Gregson.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Mary takes an interest in estate management but meets resistance from her father. Rose gets more than she bargains for at a tea dance in York.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: An eclectic mix of guests proves for a memorable house party at Downton Abbey, but the celebration takes a dark turn as the evening comes to a close.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Bates puzzles over Anna's abrupt change in behavior. Edith and Michael up the stakes of their relationship, and Alfred reveals a secret ambition.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Molesley offends Carson. Thomas tries to recruit a new ally. Feeling out of place, Branson considers a move. Bates issues an ultimatum to Mrs. Hughes.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: With Michael missing in Germany, Edith receives some unsettling news; Anna and Bates step out; Rose shakes up the family at Robert's birthday party.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: A farming crisis forces Mary and Blake to cooperate. Robert travels to America to retrieve Cora's brother while Violet falls gravely ill.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: Violet has suspicions about Edith. Mary confronts Rose about her romance, and Isobel attracts an admirer. Bates takes an unexpected day trip.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: The family readies for Rose's coming-out ball. Gillingham and Blake clash over Mary. Edith faces a difficult decision while the staff gets a day out.
episodes.title: The London Season

episodes.synopsis: Carson gets into a fight with Robert and Mrs. Hughes over a war memorial. Branson’s friendship worries Robert, and Mary knows she's ready for love.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Thomas reveals a secret, which strains the friendship between Baxter and Molesley. Rose tries to convince Robert to purchase a radio for the house.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Mary’s secret meeting may be revealed, and Violet steps in. Branson receives an interesting proposition regarding the future of Downton Abbey.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Sarah Bunting keeps causing a stir upstairs. Mary makes up her mind about Lord Gillingham. Rose’s father returns to Downton to share some news.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Branson makes a decision about Sarah. Rose encounters a handsome stranger. Violet tries to stop Isobel from making the wrong choice.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Blake’s schemes begin to be realized, and Mary must suddenly take on her rival. Edith gets shocking news and takes extreme measures.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Rose introduces Atticus and his parents at Downton. Downstairs, Molesley tries to encourage Daisy to overcome her disappointment with her studies.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: Preparation for Rose’s big day continues, but family conflict threatens to spoil the event. Edith’s arrangement works well, but how long can it last?
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: Yuletide at Downton Abbey brings romance, a heartbreaking farewell, grief over lost love and a happy reunion for the family and servants.
episodes.title: A Moorland Holiday

episodes.synopsis: A stranger appears at Downton with a message for Mary. Meanwhile, Anna suffers a new setback, and Mrs. Hughes wrestles with a delicate dilemma.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Wedding plans and fears of staff cutbacks stoke tensions among the servants, but Mary resolves to find help for Anna.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Cora wades into the hospital debate, and Mrs. Hughes finds an ally in her quest for a simple wedding. Edith faces a crisis at the magazine.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: An unexpected visitor piques Mary's interest, and a former servant returns in a new role. Daisy grows desperate to secure the farm for Mr. Mason.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Violet tries to lure a powerful figure into the hospital showdown, Barrow discovers Andy's secret, and a high-stakes dinner turns chaotic.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: As the family prepares to open the house to the public, Cora considers an intriguing offer. Daisy tries to sabotage a budding relationship.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: A trip to watch Henry Talbot race puts Mary on edge. Meanwhile, Isobel receives a puzzling invitation, and Daisy and Molesley prepare for their exams.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: New ventures prove challenging for Mrs. Patmore and Molesley. A change in Bertie's status takes the family by surprise, and a peevish Mary lashes out.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: Secret plots and life-changing moments abound as the family and staff of Downton find themselves on the brink of a new era.
episodes.title: The Finale
